Case 5-Asia-China-Hongshan-Liaoning-Torus-Single Hole Slit-Green Jade-4700-2920 BCE

Case no.: 5

Accession Number:

Formal Label: Hongshan-Jade-Liaoning-Porcine Torus-Pig Dragon-Abstract-

Display Description:

This example of a porcine torus of revolution has an opening that suggestively shows a boar’s jagged teeth.

LC Classification: GN776.3.H58

Date or Time Horizon: 4700-2920 BCE

Geographical Area: western Liaoning province

Map:

GPS coordinates: 41°15′N 119°24′E

Cultural Affiliation: Hongshan

Medium: jade

Dimensions: H 5.4 cm, W 5.4 cm, T 2.4 cm

Weight:

Condition: original

Provenance: collected near San Guan Dian Zi Cun, Lingyuan City, Liaoning Province in 1979
